OL,3,C'I've let him down': Mum's two-year
OL,4,Cwait for justice over son's killing
OL,6,F"John didn't know either person. There
OL,7,Fwas no discussions, there was no
OL,8,Fcontact with each other, it just
OL,9,Fhappened."
OL,11,FMr Smith was first attacked on Silver
OL,12,FStreet. He was then assaulted by
OL,13,Fanother person in what was believed to
OL,14,Fbe an unrelated incident on Hall Gate.
OL,16,FPart of his skull had to be removed
OL,17,Fdue to swelling on his brain. After 16
OL,18,Fmonths he had a plate fitted to his
OL,19,Fskull and seemed to be making good
OL,20,Fprogress.
